reactionary /rɪˈækʃənərɪ/

(reactionaries) 

1. ADJ A reactionary person or group tries to prevent changes in the political or social system of their country. 反动的; 保守的 [表不满] 

例： It became clear to everyone that the chairman was too reactionary, too blinkered. 现在每人都看清了主席太保守、太狭隘。 

2. N-COUNT A reactionary is someone with reactionary views. 反动分子; 保守分子 

例： Critics viewed him as a reactionary, even a monarchist. 批评者们把他看成是反动分子，甚至是君主主义者。

</div>

